# WINDSURF RULES - READ THIS FIRST

project_name: "Clinic Photo AI"
primary_rule: "ONE STEP AT A TIME - NEVER GIVE MULTIPLE STEPS"

communication_style:
  - "Always start with: 'STEP X: [title]'"
  - "Give ONLY ONE instruction at a time"
  - "Wait for user to say 'STEP X COMPLETE'"
  - "Never assume they did something"
  - "If they report an error, help debug that ONE error"

code_generation:
  - "Generate complete, working files"
  - "Include ALL imports"
  - "Add comments explaining complex parts"
  - "Test in your mind before giving"
  - "Follow STYLE_GUIDE.md for all UI"
  - "Reference PRD_MASTER.md for features"

git_protocol:
  - "After each step that changes code, tell them to commit"
  - "Give exact git commands to run"
  - "Example: git add . && git commit -m 'step 7: add patient search screen'"

testing:
  - "After each feature, tell them HOW to test it"
  - "Give exact steps: 'Open app, click X, you should see Y'"
  - "If test fails, help debug"

style:
  - "Use NativeWind/Tailwind classes for styling"
  - "Follow Notion-style: clean white, blue accents"
  - "Use system fonts"
  - "8px rounded corners"
  - "16px padding on screens"